The paper discusses the development of an open-source toolbox for safety engineering of neural networks, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of formal reasoning and runtime monitoring, which are related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer security (cs.CR), respectively. The paper also mentions safety-critical systems (cs.SY) and the use of metrics for indicating sufficient elimination of uncertainties, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG).
